<quantity box="[151,240,765,790]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,549,970]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,490,801,826]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Marwick, 1931" authorityName="Marwick" authorityYear="1931" box="[503,748,801,826]" class="Gastropoda" family="Architectonicidae" genus="Discotectonica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="discus">
<emphasis box="[503,748,801,826]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Discotectonica discus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed from the Lusitanic province to West Africa and the Mediterranean, as well as in the Caribbean area; it is a rare species dwelling on circalittoral to bathyal mud (Melone &amp; Taviani 1984; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poppe" box="[445,676,874,898]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" refString="Poppe, G. T. &amp; Goto, Y. (1991) European Seashells. Volume I. (Polyplacophora, Caudofoveata, Solenogastra, Gastropoda). Verlag Christa Hemmen, Wiesbaden, 352 pp." type="book" year="1991">
Poppe &amp; 
<collectingRegion box="[552,608,874,898]" country="Malta" name="Zebbug" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Goto</collectingRegion>
1991
</bibRefCitation>
). In the Santa Maria di Leuca 
<collectionCode box="[1018,1082,874,898]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15029" name="Central Wyoming College" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">CWC</collectionCode>
biotope, it was found on living colonies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mastrototaro et al. 2010" authorityName="Mastrototaro et al." authorityYear="2010" box="[281,799,909,934]" class="Anthozoa" family="Oculinidae" genus="Madrepora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis box="[281,499,909,934]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Madrepora oculata</emphasis>
(Mastrototaro 
<emphasis box="[667,723,909,934]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2010)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
